@node intro "Introduction"

  @{b}Introduction@{ub}


  Choowin is a little tool comparable to the windows taskbar; it
  gives a list of current windows on all public screens. If you click
  on an entry, this window (and its screen if necessary) will be
  brought to the front and will be activated.
  
  That's not all, just with v1.0 you have the possibiliy to enter
  your programs in the tooltypes that can be started via Workbench.

  Look into the tooltypes (click on the Choowin icon and select
  Icon->Information from the Menu), and you will see how to
  @{" configure your start menu " link use}.
@endnode

@node require "Requirements and Compatibility"

  @{b}Requirements and compatibility@{ub}


  Choowin uses reaction and therefore requires at least OS3.5 or
  newer versions.
  
  It starts programs like double clicked on WB and needs one of the
  system commands that are new in OS 3.5.
  This could be a problem if you are using DOpus since these commands
  are not available (but DOpus has itself start menus).

@endnode

@node install "Installation and deinstallation"


  @{b}Installation and deinstallation@{ub}


  Please use the installation script @{i}Choowin.install @{ui} that
  prepares everything to use Choowin.

  In fact, there are only two important files: the program itself and
  this manual. So you can put them where you want.
  You can also drop the program in WBStartup to start it automatically
  (this requires the tooltype DONOTWAIT that should already be set; in
  RAWWBInfo there is a gadget you can check).

  To remove Choowin, just delete these two files.

@endnode

@node config "Configuration"

  @{b}Configuration@{ub}

  First you have to edit the tooltypes to fit your choices:


  @{b}Window layout@{ub}

  POSX,    position of Choowin on the Workbench screen (use a high
  POSY:    value to bring it to the right or bottom border).
           When on the right border, Choowin has a problem when it
           first opens program subwindows because it cannot
           estimate the window width.

           Example: POSX=0
                    POSY=700

  WIDTH,   now obsolete. The window size is automatically chosen.
  HEIGHT:

  SCREEN:  public screen where choowin shall appear, either the
           correct PubScreenName if known or a significant part of it

           Example: SCREEN=AWEB

  PATTERN: specify the filename of a pattern that is used as
           background.
           To make the window "transparent" you could copy a part
           of your screen background, save it and give the filename
           to choowin (there are many programs in Aminet that can
           store a part of a window or screen).
           You then will also want to set NOBORDER.

           Example: PATTERN=WB:Prefs/Presets/Patterns/pattern.iff

  INNERPATTERN: specify the filename of a pattern that is used as
           background for the menu window. There are three
           choices:

           If you do not specify it, the window is filled with the
           background color.
           If you use "INNERPATTERN", the standard Reaction pattern
           is used.
           If you use "INNERPATTERN=...", the given image is used
           as pattern.

  ALIGN:     how the text in the lists is aligned. Possible values
             are LEFT, RIGHT, CENTER.
             Standard is LEFT.
             Example: ALIGN=CENTER

  DELAY:     how many seconds shall the list window remain open.
             Standard is 2 seconds (approximately).
             Example: DELAY=4

  NOSTART:   do not display start button
             Example: NOSTART

  NOWINDOWS: do not display windows button
             Example: NOWINDOWS

  NOBORDER:  do not display window border
             Example: NOBORDER


  @{b}Starting programs@{ub}

  If you want to use Choowin to start programs, you have to give it
  a list of files. You can add a file by specifying START=... or
  group them with GROUP=...
  The files appear in the same order as the tooltype strings.

  GROUP:    the beginning and name of a group of programs. There can
            follow several START or GROUP entries, and each group must
            be terminated by ENDGROUP.

            Example: GROUP=Applications

  START:    the program to be started. First write the name for the
            entry, then a comma and the filename.
            Can't stand at the top of the list.
         
            Example: START=AWeb,aweb3:aweb-ii

  ENDGROUP: end of the group.

            Example: ENDGROUP


  @{b}Displaying windows@{ub}

  UNNAMED: also windows without titles are shown with their position
           (as "Unnamed at (x,y)")

           Example: UNNAMED

  FILTER:  enter name pattern of windows that shall not be shown,
           enclosed in quotes and case sensitive.
           Can be used several times.

           Example: FILTER="Unnamed at (0,0)"

@endnode

@node use "Usage"

  @{b}Usage@{ub}

  Start the program by double clicking on it. You can also drop it
  in WBStartup to start it automatically, then use the tooltype
  DONOTWAIT (it should already be set; in RAWWBInfo there is a gadget
  you can check).

  When Choowin is started, there appears a window with one or two
  buttons somewhere on the screen (depending on the current
  tooltypes).

  You can start a program with the left (start) button; click on it
  and choose the program. You can click on a group, what opens the
  next window with the contents of this group.

  When you want to see a specific window, click on the window gadget
  and then on the entry which shows the window title.

  If you click on any other area or press any key, or the right mouse
  button, or do nothing for some seconds (see @{" DELAY " link config}),
  the menu will be closed.

  To quit the program, press 'q' when a list is open.

@endnode

@node problems "Problems"

  @{b}Problems@{ub}

  o  When you activate the Choowin window and then click on the
     Workbench or a WB window, the mouse doesn't move some time.
     That's due to the design of the Workbench and can't be changed.
     (Thanks to Jochen Becher for the explanation!)
     Please press the right mouse button or a key, or wait until the
     window is closed.

@endnode

@node hist "History"

  @{b}History@{ub}

  V1.11, 28.10.01:

    - Added German manual.

  V1.1, 17.04.01:

    - changed handling and display of lists: patterns can be used, you can
      build trees of programs, the window shows all the entries

    - added the tooltype PATTERN where you can specify your own pattern for the
      buttons, INNERPATTERN to specify a pattern for the lists

    - added the tooltype DELAY that determines the time in secs after which the
      window is automatically closed

    - added the tooltype ALIGN to decide how the text is aligned in the lists

    - added the tooltype NOBORDER that makes the window border disappear

    - added the tooltype ENDGROUP which allows to specify program trees

    - added manual

  V1.0, 07.04.01:
    - added complete start menu
    - changed the ugly icon into glowy icon
    - added tooltypes FILTER,GROUP,START
@endnode

